contracts/PRODUCTION_SET.md:104:| `VaultInfrastructure` | **MOVED TO `contracts/legacy/` 2026-05-16** | The file's M-21 Architecture Note already self-documented that CardBoundVault + VaultHub had superseded UserVaultLegacy. Confirmed at move time: VaultHub provides all three lookup functions `VaultRegistry` needs (`vaultOf`, `ownerOfVault`, `isVault`) via auto-generated getters on its public mappings, and is already in active use for those calls by `FraudRegistry`, `VFIDETermLoan`, and `VaultRecoveryClaim`. The deprecated force-recovery functions in `IVaultInfrastructure` are non-custodial-removed and aren't called by V1 paths. Retained in legacy for reference / backward-compat with any pre-existing UserVaultLegacy deployments. |
